{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":885,"text":"So I've been thinking about the difference between"},{"time":2407,"text":"the résumé virtues and \nthe eulogy virtues."},{"time":5541,"text":"The résumé virtues are the\nones you put on your résumé,"},{"time":8443,"text":"which are the skills \nyou bring to the marketplace."},{"time":11909,"text":"The eulogy virtues are the ones"},{"time":13647,"text":"that get mentioned in the eulogy,"},{"time":15129,"text":"which are deeper: who are you, \nin your depth,"},{"time":18067,"text":"what is the nature of your relationships,"},{"time":19843,"text":"are you bold, loving, dependable, consistency?"},{"time":23407,"text":"And most of us, including \nme, would say"},{"time":24901,"text":"that the eulogy virtues are the\nmore important of the virtues."},{"time":28127,"text":"But at least in my case, \nare they the ones that"},{"time":30200,"text":"I think about the most? \nAnd the answer is no."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33002,"text":"So I've been thinking about that problem,"},{"time":35295,"text":"and a thinker who has \nhelped me think about it"},{"time":36463,"text":"is a guy named Joseph Soloveitchik, who was a rabbi"},{"time":38076,"text":"who wrote a book called \"The\nLonely Man Of Faith\" in 1965."},{"time":41446,"text":"Soloveitchik said there are two sides of our natures,"},{"time":44766,"text":"which he called Adam I\nand Adam II."},{"time":47156,"text":"Adam I is the worldly, ambitious,"},{"time":48888,"text":"external side of our nature."},{"time":51111,"text":"He wants to build, create,\ncreate companies,"},{"time":53184,"text":"create innovation."},{"time":54730,"text":"Adam II is the humble\nside of our nature."},{"time":57468,"text":"Adam II wants not only \nto do good but to be good,"},{"time":60285,"text":"to live in a way internally"},{"time":62232,"text":"that honors God, creation and our possibilities."},{"time":66035,"text":"Adam I wants to conquer the world."},{"time":67923,"text":"Adam II wants to hear \na calling and obey the world."},{"time":70687,"text":"Adam I savors accomplishment."},{"time":73175,"text":"Adam II savors inner \nconsistency and strength."},{"time":75857,"text":"Adam I asks how things work."},{"time":78600,"text":"Adam II asks why we're here."},{"time":80918,"text":"Adam I's motto is \"success.\""},{"time":83022,"text":"Adam II's motto is \"love, redemption and return.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":87268,"text":"And Soloveitchik argued \nthat these two sides"},{"time":89118,"text":"of our nature are \nat war with each other."},{"time":91766,"text":"We live in perpetual self-confrontation"},{"time":93830,"text":"between the external success and the internal value."},{"time":97094,"text":"And the tricky thing, \nI'd say, about these"},{"time":99578,"text":"two sides of our nature is they work"},{"time":101270,"text":"by different logics."},{"time":103680,"text":"The external logic is \nan economic logic:"},{"time":105914,"text":"input leads to output, \nrisk leads to reward."},{"time":109380,"text":"The internal side of our nature"},{"time":111156,"text":"is a moral logic and \noften an inverse logic."},{"time":114577,"text":"You have to give to receive."},{"time":116451,"text":"You have to surrender \nto something outside yourself"},{"time":118167,"text":"to gain strength within yourself."},{"time":120449,"text":"You have to conquer the\ndesire to get what you want."},{"time":122770,"text":"In order to fulfill yourself,\nyou have to forget yourself."},{"time":125561,"text":"In order to find yourself, \nyou have to lose yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129873,"text":"We happen to live in a society \nthat favors Adam I,"},{"time":132809,"text":"and often neglects Adam II."},{"time":135049,"text":"And the problem is, that turns\nyou into a shrewd animal"},{"time":138281,"text":"who treats life as a game,"},{"time":139838,"text":"and you become a cold, \ncalculating creature"},{"time":142563,"text":"who slips into a sort of mediocrity"},{"time":145369,"text":"where you realize there's a difference"},{"time":146829,"text":"between your desired \nself and your actual self."},{"time":149401,"text":"You're not earning the sort of eulogy you want,"},{"time":153374,"text":"you hope someone will give to you."},{"time":154934,"text":"You don't have the \ndepth of conviction."},{"time":156660,"text":"You don't have an emotional sonorousness."},{"time":159197,"text":"You don't have \ncommitment to tasks"},{"time":160966,"text":"that would take more than a lifetime to commit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164180,"text":"I was reminded of a common\nresponse through history"},{"time":167627,"text":"of how you build a solid Adam II,"},{"time":170389,"text":"how you build a depth of character."},{"time":172399,"text":"Through history, people \nhave gone back"},{"time":175124,"text":"into their own pasts,"},{"time":177010,"text":"sometimes to a precious \ntime in their life,"},{"time":179260,"text":"to their childhood,"},{"time":180719,"text":"and often, the mind \ngravitates in the past"},{"time":184685,"text":"to a moment of shame,"},{"time":186073,"text":"some sin committed, \nsome act of selfishness,"},{"time":189000,"text":"an act of omission, of shallowness,"},{"time":191290,"text":"the sin of anger, the sin of self-pity,"},{"time":194033,"text":"trying to be a people-pleaser, \na lack of courage."},{"time":197618,"text":"Adam I is built by \nbuilding on your strengths."},{"time":202313,"text":"Adam II is built by fighting \nyour weaknesses."},{"time":206409,"text":"You go into yourself, \nyou find the sin"},{"time":209267,"text":"which you've committed over\nand again through your life,"},{"time":210939,"text":"your signature sin"},{"time":212740,"text":"out of which the others emerge,"},{"time":215431,"text":"and you fight that sin and you wrestle with that sin,"},{"time":218295,"text":"and out of that wrestling, \nthat suffering,"},{"time":221431,"text":"then a depth of character is constructed."},{"time":225049,"text":"And we're often not\ntaught to recognize"},{"time":226951,"text":"the sin in ourselves,"},{"time":228087,"text":"in that we're not taught in this culture"},{"time":229935,"text":"how to wrestle with it,"},{"time":231882,"text":"how to confront it, \nand how to combat it."},{"time":234555,"text":"We live in a culture \nwith an Adam I mentality"},{"time":237885,"text":"where we're inarticulate \nabout Adam II."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241054,"text":"Finally, Reinhold Niebuhr"},{"time":242710,"text":"summed up the confrontation, the fully lived"},{"time":244845,"text":"Adam I and Adam II life, this way:"},{"time":248398,"text":"\"Nothing that is worth doing\ncan be achieved in our lifetime;"},{"time":251660,"text":"therefore we must \nbe saved by hope."},{"time":254042,"text":"Nothing which is true or\nbeautiful or good makes"},{"time":257148,"text":"complete sense in any immediate context of history;"},{"time":260104,"text":"therefore we must be saved by faith."},{"time":262782,"text":"Nothing we do, however virtuous,\ncan be accomplished alone;"},{"time":266672,"text":"therefore we must \nbe saved by love."},{"time":269718,"text":"No virtuous act is quite as virtuous"},{"time":272155,"text":"from the standpoint of our friend\nor foe as from our own standpoint."},{"time":276141,"text":"Therefore we must be saved \nby that final form of love,"},{"time":278968,"text":"which is forgiveness.”"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280604,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}